Git is distributed file system (DFCS)
Repo: Each user must have a local copy of the entire project or the history of the project. That is calles repo. 
Examples: Github, Gitlab, Bitbucket
Advantage: User can work offline and can easily synchronize repos.

Git is a free and opensource software project meaning that the project is publically available. 
Main git commands:
add
commit
pull
push
log status
flags
